<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="169" type="notes.">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">Notes.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="169">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9541" author="Bolivar, I" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique" pageId="11" pageNumber="178" refId="B6" refString="Bolivar, I, 1898. . https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9541" url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9541" year="1898">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bolívar">Bolivar</normalizedToken>
(1898)
</bibRefCitation>
described the species under the section Metrodorae as belonging to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xistra" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">Xistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while earlier he described 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. contractus" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="contractus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">L. contractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the section Tettigiae, assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Paratettix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paratettix" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">Paratettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two sections were distinguished by morphology of the lateral 
<normalizedToken originalValue="lobes—projected">lobes-projected</normalizedToken>
sidewards in Metrodorae, directed downwards in Tettigiae. When comparing types, I did not see differences in this feature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="169">
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="169" refId="B14">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1939)
</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. contractus" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" rank="subspecies" species="contractus" subspecies="tricristatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">L. contractus tricristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. contractus" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="contractus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">L. contractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished from the nominal by smaller size, sharper keeled prozonal carinae and, in lateral view, clearly visible fastigial horns (above the eyes). 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. c." pageId="2" pageNumber="169" rank="subspecies" species="c." subspecies="tricristatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">L. c. tricristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be slightly smaller and should have wavy margins of the fore legs (
<bibRefCitation author="Guenther, K" journalOrPublisher="Arbeiten ueber Morphologische und Taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem" pageId="11" pageNumber="178" pagination="257 - 263" refId="B10" refString="Guenther, K, 1935. Acrydiinen (Orth. Acrididae) aus dem mittleren Ostborneo, gesammelt von H. C. Siebers 1925. . Arbeiten ueber Morphologische und Taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem 2: 257 - 263" title="Acrydiinen (Orth. Acrididae) aus dem mittleren Ostborneo, gesammelt von H. C. Siebers 1925." volume="2" year="1935">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
1935
</bibRefCitation>
). All these features are, however, in the range of variation of the species and are not of diagnostic value. Moreover, I did not find reported differences when comparing the types. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="169" refId="B25">Otte (1997)</bibRefCitation>
gave the specific status to the subspecies only with the reason of occurrence on different islands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="169">
All these data prove that 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. tricristatus" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="tricristatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">L. tricristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bolívar">Bolivar</normalizedToken>
, 1898) is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. contractus" pageId="2" pageNumber="169" rank="species" species="contractus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="169">L. contractus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
